                <summary>The usual arguments for the protective tariff keeping money at home by
                    protecting local manufacturers. Article mostly notable for naming the textile
                    firm of Black and White, who produce flannel blankets, jeans, shawls, satinetts
                    and carpets at the Franklin Woolen Factory near Fayetteville.</summary>
                <note/>
