                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>Notes the meeting of the States-Rights Democratic faction at Altoona. The
                    group, led by John Forney, resolved not to nominate a state ticket, but demanded
                    that Democrats honor the Buchanan position stated in the Harrisburg Convention
                    of April 13, 1859.</summary>
